-- Reliant Energy names new chief executive
-- 
-- Thu Feb 22, 2007 8:54am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/22/us-reliantenergy-ceo-idUSWEN463820070222

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Reliant Energy Inc. RRI.N on Thursday said Mark Jacobs would succeed Joel Staff as its chief executive officer, effective as of the company's 2007 annual meeting. 


 Jacobs, currently executive vice president and chief financial officer, will become president and CEO, the power company said in a statement. The Houston-based company said Staff will remain on the board of directors as non-executive chairman. Reliant also said Brian Landrum, currently executive vice president, operations, will be named chief operating officer.